@startuml task-lifecycle
' AgentTask state machine.
' Source of truth: docs/src/controller/task-lifecycle.md
!include _style.puml

state "Pending" as Pending
state "Provisioning" as Provisioning
state "Running" as Running
state "Completing" as Completing
state "Succeeded" as Succeeded
state "Failed" as Failed
state "TimedOut" as TimedOut
state "Terminating" as Terminating
state "any state" as AnyState $mutedBg

note right of Provisioning : creating Pod/PVC
note right of Completing : collecting artifacts,\nscheduling teardown

' ---- Main path ----
[*] --> Pending
Pending --> Provisioning : references validated
Provisioning --> Running : Pod Ready
Running --> Completing : completion signal,\ntimeout, or exit
Completing --> Succeeded : success reported
Completing --> Failed : failure reported
Completing --> TimedOut : timeout hit

' ---- Failure and retry paths ----
Pending -[#0D47A1]-> Failed : spec irreconcilable
Provisioning -[#0D47A1]-> Failed : Pod-start error
Running -[#0D47A1]-> Failed : Pod disruption
Failed -[#0D47A1]-> Provisioning : retry while\nstatus.retries < backoffLimit

' ---- Teardown ----
AnyState --> Terminating : deletion requested
Succeeded -[#0D47A1]-> Terminating : ttlSecondsAfterFinished\nexpired
Failed -[#0D47A1]-> Terminating : ttlSecondsAfterFinished\nexpired
TimedOut -[#0D47A1]-> Terminating : ttlSecondsAfterFinished\nexpired

note bottom of Failed
  Pending: PersistenceNotAllowed or
  ClassConstraintViolation. Not retried.
  ....
  Provisioning and Running failures are
  retried under backoffLimit.
end note

' ---- Layout hints ----
Succeeded -[hidden]-> AnyState
TimedOut -[hidden]-> AnyState
@enduml
